# Simple List App

A small React Native + TypeScript list app built with Expo. The app is intentionally minimal but demonstrates common list behaviors and a multi-list layout with tabs.

## What It Does
- Creates a simple list app with a bit of dummy data so the UI has content on first launch.
- Has an icon button to create a new list entry.
- Has an icon button to delete a list entry.
- Can select multiple items and combine them into a single item.
- Can support multiple lists using tabs across the top.

## Expected UI Behavior
- The top area shows tabs for each list. Tapping a tab switches the active list.
- Each list shows items with a selectable state.
- When two or more items are selected, a Combine action merges them into one item.
- Add and Delete actions are represented as icons for quick access.

## Sample Data
The app boots with a small set of items, for example:
- Buy coffee
- Read a chapter
- Walk the dog

## Tech Stack
- React Native
- Expo
- TypeScript

## Running The App
1. Install dependencies with your package manager.
2. Start the Expo dev server.
3. Open on iOS Simulator, Android Emulator, or Expo Go.

